OL,3,C'We let people down,' says health
OL,4,Cminister after infected blood scandal
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FReport author Sir Brian Langstaff
OL,8,Fconcluded "the chief responsibility
OL,9,Ffor the failings lies with successive
OL,10,Fgovernments", and that they "showed
OL,11,Flittle interest in finding the truth".
OL,13,FThe scandal happened in the 1970s and
OL,14,F1980s, and after decades of
OL,15,Fcampaigning for justice, victims and
OL,16,Ftheir families are finally getting
OL,17,Fanswers in a milestone report.
