OL,3,C'We let people down,' says health
OL,4,Cminister after infected blood scandal
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FIn his damming report, Sir Brian said
OL,8,F"lives, dreams, friendships, families
OL,9,Fand finances were destroyed" by the
OL,10,Fscandal that "could have been
OL,11,Fprevented and should have been".
OL,13,FHe places the majority of the blame
OL,14,Ffor the disaster on "successive
OL,15,Fgovernments," saying they showed
OL,16,F"little interest in finding the truth,
OL,17,Flistening to those infected, or taking
OL,18,Faction," and refused to admit
OL,19,Fresponsibility in order to "save face".
