OL,3,C'We let people down,' says health
OL,4,Cminister after infected blood scandal
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,F"First to apologies for the failure in
OL,8,Fblood policy and blood products, and
OL,9,Fthe devastating and so often fatal
OL,10,Fimpact its had on so many lives,
OL,11,Fincluding the impact of testaments
OL,12,Fthat were known or proved to be
OL,13,Fcontaminated, the failure to respond
OL,14,Fto the risk of imported concentrates,
OL,15,Fthe failure to prioritise self-
OL,16,Fsufficiency in blood, the failure to
OL,17,Fintroduce screening services sooner,
OL,18,Fand the mismanagement of the response
OL,19,Fto the emergence of Aids and hepatitis
OL,20,Fviruses amongst infected blood victims.
